<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/64258130-rick"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1485374175i/64258130._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/64258130-rick">Rick</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">First of all; this is the third of five books in the Hitchhiker&apos;s Trilogy. Read it third, not first. If you&apos;d read the the first two you&apos;d know the an<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">First of all; this is the third of five books in the Hitchhiker's Trilogy. Read it third, not first. If you'd read the the first two you'd know the answer to your question.<br /><br />There is no plot. Anything in any of these books that in anyway resembles a "plot" was put there by Adams just to throw you off the scent. Don't expect a plot, don't look for a plot; just read and enjoy. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
